children.text: The 90x35mm pine ceiling joists installed in this area exceed the maximum span of 1700mm (single span), or 2200mm (continuous span).

The relevant Australian Standard AS 1684 Residential Timber-Framed Construction, in Table 21 - Ceiling Joists for 90x35mm MGP10 Pine, only allows for a span of 1700mm (single span), or 2200mm (continuous span). See below;

As these maximum spans have been exceeded, which could result in the ceiling sagging (or failure), the builder should either upgrade the timber size/strength grade, or provide additional supports to reduce the spans to within these requirements.
